Sir Billy Connolly has received his first dose of the coronavirus vaccine.The comedian's wife Pamela Stephenson shared an image on social media of the 78-year-old wearing a mask with a plaster on his left arm.Alongside the picture, Ms Stephenson wrote: "Thank God... Billy had his first Covid vaccine today!"Sir Billy, who lives in Florida, was diagnosed with Parkinson's disease in 2013 and announced he was "finished with stand-up" last year.He said at the time: "The Parkinson's has made my brain work differently and you need to have a good brain for comedy."Sir Billy joins famous faces including actress Dame Judi Dench, broadcaster Sir David Attenborough and actor Sir Ian McKellen in receiving the vaccine.Hollywood star and former California governor Arnold Schwarzenegger also shared a video of him receiving the jab earlier this week.Biden to halt new drilling on federal landsOil and gas extraction will be paused and wind energy will expand under Joe Biden's climate plan.AstraZeneca-EU row escalates over vaccine shortageGymnast's 'black excellence' routine goes viralThe homeless addict who became a professorWhy convicting Trump just got a lot harderWhen your 'pandemic puppy' doesn't work outDave Grohl: 'I dreamt I was shot in the back'The comic in jail for jokes he didn't crackA raccoon, pony and other White House petsWho's behind the recent killings in Iraq? VideoWho's behind the recent killings in Iraq?Holocaust Memorial Day 2021: 'It's sad when I sit there alone' VideoHolocaust Memorial Day 2021: 'It's sad when I sit there alone'The child environmentalist receiving death threatsFootball phrases15 sayings from around the worldGymnast's 'black excellence' routine goes viral1AstraZeneca-EU row escalates over vaccine shortage2Juno actor Elliot Page to divorce Emma Portner3Why convicting Trump just got a lot harder4Biden raises election meddling in call with Putin5Bank boss gets $10m pay cut for Malaysia scandal6Capitol riots: Who has the FBI arrested so far?7When your